 (7,6,1,1,'2011-12-16','<ul>\r\n<li>Worked on revising the SLM IM for implementation</li>\r\n<li>Updated the SLM timeline for implementation</li>\r\n<li>Discuss the Section 508 Evaluation form with Mrs. Laura Bell</li>\r\n<li>Provided the DOI Section 508 Evaluation form to Mrs. Laura Bell</li>\r\n<li>Worked on finalizing the SLM IM for review</li>\r\n<li>Worked with Lauren Clapp to draft a Note to Review for the SLM IM that has to be submitted for review</li>\r\n<li>Worked on defining the SLM Roles for Ms. Levine from a previous meeting. &nbsp;Worked on defining: Business Project Manager, Technical Project Manager, Operational Project Manager</li>\r\n<li>Reviewed WO-300 Roles and responsibilities that was submitted by John Broderick</li>\r\n<li>Helped Naomi draft an email to CPIC regarding the status of them reviewing the SLM documenation</li>\r\n<li>Worked on making some additional changes to the SLM handbook regarding the role and responsibilities of CPIC</li>\r\n</ul>','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"background-image: url(../../../images/body_bg.jpeg); background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: 1.2em; height: 100%; outline-width: 2px !important; outline-style: solid !important; outline-color: rgba(254, 192, 26, 0.699219) !important; outline-offset: 1px !important; background-repeat: repeat no-repeat; margin: 8px;\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Completed and submitted an updated draft of the SLM IM for implementation to Mr. Samuels</li>\r\n<li>Completed and submitted an updated draft of the SLM timeline for implementation to Mr. Samuels</li>\r\n<li>Provided a copy of the DOI Section 508 Evaluation form to Mrs. Laura Bell to keep in their document repository</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.2em;\">Completed and submitted the updated draft SLM IM for review</span></li>\r\n<li>Completed and submitted a draft Note to Review for the SLM IM that has to be submitted for review to Lauren</li>\r\n<li>Completed and submitted the draft definitions of SLM Roles for Ms. Levine from a previous meeting. Submitted definitions for: Business Project Manager, Technical Project Manager, Operational Project Manager (change to: IRM Analyst)</li>\r\n<li>Provided my feedback regarding the WO-300 Roles and responsibilities submitted by John Broderick</li>\r\n<li>Submitted the draft email I help Naomi draft to CPIC regarding the status of them reviewing the SLM documenation</li>\r\n<li>Completed making changes to the SLM handbook regarding the role and responsibilities of CPIC </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<ul>\r\n<li>Had a brief meeting with Laura Bell regarding the Section 508 Evaluation form. 12-13-11. &nbsp;Discuss Section 508 role in the SLM process and provide Mrs. Bell a Section 508 Evaluation template since they did not have one. &nbsp;The template will be used to perform the required actions that they are required to perform.</li>\r\n<li>Had a meeting Naomi to review the GeoComm project documents. 12-14-11. &nbsp;Discussed some changes to the templates she was currently working on for the GeoComm project. &nbsp;Looked at whether the changes would have any serious impact on the overall document. &nbsp;She also recommend adding a section for functional requirements to the template that would make it easier for the business to fill out.</li>\r\n<li>Had a meeting with Naomi to assist in review the roles and responibilities in the SLM handbook. 12-15-11. &nbsp;We met to re-review the roles and responsibilities of all the supporting divisions and made some changes based on our discussion with CPIC. &nbsp;We are also going to make some suggestions to Mr. Samuels regarding adding CPIC to other phases in the SLM process for checks and balances. &nbsp;CPIC should be reviewing/performing actions in just about every phase. &nbsp;Currently CPIC noted they only need to be in 2 phases (Initiation &amp; Requirements Analysis)</li>\r\n<li>Brief meeting with Mr. Samuels regarding the SLM Roles definitions. 12-15-11. &nbsp;Met to discuss the roles Ms. Levine wanted us to define: Business Project Manager, Technical Project Manager, and Operations Project Manager. &nbsp;We discuss these different areas and I suggested we change the Operations Project Manager to Business &amp; Technology Analyst. &nbsp;After discussing Mr. Samuels decided it needed to be changed and wanted it changed to IRM Analyst.</li>\r\n</ul>','<p>None at this time</p>','<p>None at this time</p>',2,4,'2011-12-19 15:35:31',6,'2011-12-20 23:32:49'),
