 (10,3,2,1,'2011-12-30','<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Continued to prepare the presentation to the ITIB for requisition of planning funds on 12/27/11.&nbsp; Spoke with Beth via conference call regarding the presentation and provided her with an early draft copy on 12/27/11.&nbsp; She will review with other team members and provide feedback.</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed functional requirements feedback on 12/27/11 and 12/28/11 and communicated concerns to Beth.&nbsp; The concern is that some of the feedback speaks to a solution instead of focusing on functionality.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Mohammad on 12/28/11 to discuss the 200 projects that he is working with in order to understand the relationship to GPI.&nbsp; Form his point of view, the systems that he is involved with will not affect GPI.</p>\r\n<p>Attended WebEx/Conf call on 12/29/11 regarding functional requirements.&nbsp; Beth asked that I speak to the issue of defining requirements and not solutions.&nbsp; The team members on the call were very receptive to this however there still seems to be some confusion in regards to the scope.&nbsp; I stated that WO 500 could not define their scope for them and that they should contact Mike Nedd if they needed scope clarification and he could work with the ITIB to provide answers.</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed and provided comments on 12/30/11 in regards to the meeting notes from the conference call on 12/29/11.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 12/28/11 to discuss the Geospatial Publication Alignment with SLM.&nbsp; We discussed ways of focusing a business on the needs versus the solution.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 12/30/11 to discuss system duplication issues within in BLM and how SLM can help address the issue.&nbsp; We discussed the need to emphasize the importance of Enterprise Architecture before starting any project.</p>\r\n<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Reviewed the New Media Strategy and Presentation on 12/30/11.&nbsp