 (11,6,1,1,'2011-12-30','<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Reviewed additional GeoComm project documents for Naomi that she has recently completed/edited.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Had discussion with Naomi regarding the GeoComm project she is currently working on.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Worked on the SLM Acquisition Strategy template. &nbsp;Make the changes noted by Kim Ashby (IT Acquisitions) in her review of this document.&nbsp; Will need to have her review this document again.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Worked on making the recommended changes to the SLM Business Case template.&nbsp; Added a section for functional requirements.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Worked on the SLM Project Charter template.&nbsp; Made some changes/edits to make the roles and responsibilities easy to understand.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Had several discussions and emails with Mr. Leonard Gore (from BLM GIS group) to discuss their current need for help in the area of GIS.&nbsp; They are looking for some help to get some flex viewer maps online that will benefit the Washington Office.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Worked on getting together some records management templates that we can add to the SLM repository.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in;\">Followed up with Lauren Clapp and the status of the SLM note to reviewer and SLM IM.</span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12pt;\">Completed review the GeoComm document for Naomi and provided my feedback.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt;\">Discussed with Naomi how we can get GeoComm aligned with SLM.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">Discussed with Naomi BLM system duplication issues.</span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Met with Naomi to review additional draft GeoComm project documents. 12-27 and 12-28. Reviewed several of GeoComm project document to ensure consistancy, good quality and overall made sure the documents made sense.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Also met with Naomi to discuss a few of the current issues the GeoComm business project team is having regarding defining boundaries for the scope of the project.&nbsp; 12-28 and 12-29. The business is currently having problems/issues in deciding what to include in the scope of the project.&nbsp; Looking at how we can assist the business by providing clear understanding of what they have to do.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in;\">Met with Mr. Leonard Gore (from BLM GIS group) to discuss their current need for help if the area of GIS.&nbsp; 12-28. &nbsp;They are looking for some help to get some flex viewer maps online that will benefit the Washington Office.&nbsp; We met at his office and he walked me through the manual process of how they currently create maps that they use.&nbsp; They are currently looking for ways to automate this manual process and for an easy way to easily create new maps in the future.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Had several phone conversations with Mr. Leonard Gore to discuss some emails that he wanted me to look at relating to GIS. 12-28 and 12-29.&nbsp; Sent me some emails of potential solutions he was currently looking at.&nbsp; We discussed them and will be further talking next week after the New Year&rsquo;s break is over.&nbsp; Mr. Leonard Gore also mentioned that he will talk to Mr. Samuels to see how we can help him with this effort.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Met with Naomi to discuss how we can get GeoComm aligned with SLM. 12-28</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Met with Naomi to discuss the current problem BLM has with duplicate systems. 12-30</span></li>\r\n</ul>','<p><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa;\">None at this time</span></p>','<p><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa;\">None at this time</span></p>',2,4,'2011-12-30 17:48:25',NULL,'2012-01-05 01:33:18'),
 (12,3,2,1,'2012-01-06','<p><strong>Unified Communication</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Mohammad to discuss Unified Communication on 1/3/11.&nbsp; Forwarded him a presentation regarding how to present it to upper management.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth 1/4/11 regarding WO 300\'s presentation to Mike Nedd regarding the status and the scope concerns.&nbsp; Compiled slides for their afternoon presentation.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq requested that we present information regarding the status of GPI to Ms. Levine on 1/4/11 prior to her meeting with Mr. Nedd on 1/5/11.&nbsp; Prepared a status presentation to present to Ms. Levine on 1/4/11.&nbsp; The presentation was approved by Mr. Samuels.&nbsp; Al\'Tariq, Mr. Lewis and myself met with Ms. Levine on 1/4/11 to discuss GPI and AFMSS.&nbsp; Ms. Levine reviewed the information and informed us that the ITIB would likely be postponed.&nbsp; She informed us that user groups needed to be part of our effort and that a lead should be chosen outside of WO300 and WO500.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Mohammad on 1/4/11 to dicuss NISMS and GPI scopes.&nbsp; He was unsure of NISMS scope so we could not define overlap.&nbsp; We disussed the need for a site where everyone could share information about projects they are working on and the status.</p>\r\n<p><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <w:WordDocument> <w:View>Normal</w:View> <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom> <w:TrackMoves /> <w:TrackFormatting /> <w:PunctuationKerning /> <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas /> <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid> <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent> <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText> <w:DoNotPromoteQF /> <w:LidThemeOther>EN-US</w:LidThemeOther> <w:LidThemeAsian>X-NONE</w:LidThemeAsian> <w:LidThemeComplexScript>X-NONE</w:LidThemeComplexScript> <w:Compatibility> <w:BreakWrappedTables /> <w:SnapToGridInCell /> <w:WrapTextWithPunct /> <w:UseAsianBreakRules /> <w:DontGrowAutofit /> <w:SplitPgBreakAndPar