;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Mr. Samuels, Ms. Levine, Mr. Nedd, Beth, Dan and Tim S. on 1/5/11 regarding the Geospatial Publication Investment(GPI) and its scope.&nbsp; The GPI team proposed creating a Bureau wide effort instead of just a WO 300 effort.&nbsp; Ms. Levine and Mr. Need both agreed that it was a good goal.&nbsp; Ms. Levine reinforced that WO 300 needs to work with the other Directorates in order to gain buy in.&nbsp; Ms. Levine also stated that she wants an end user team established with a team lead.&nbsp; Beth agreed that this was a good idea and feasible.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Ms. Levine also announced that the ITIB will be postponed.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Discussed the creation of a formal user group on 1/5/11 with Beth and Al\'Tariq.&nbsp; Beth thinks this is a great idea because it will ensure requirements are gathered while maintaining a balance between WO 300, WO 500 and users.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Beth requested additional information regarding a presentation that  Patrick did.&nbsp; I will work with Patrick when he returns to gather  information.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Submitted email request to Mr. Smauels on 1/3/11 in regards to the status of the New Media strategy.&nbsp; He provided a verbal response that he had not submitted the newest version to the teams.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Other</strong></p>\r\n<p>Attended staff meeting on 1/4/11. Mr. Samuels emphasized the need to understand WO 500 goals and the roles that each of us play.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 1/4/11 to discuss GPI\'s status.&nbsp; We looked at strategy\'s to ensure that we were pursuing the best approach since we inserted GPI into SLM after the project had started.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred to discuss NOC\'s concerns on 1/6/11.&nbsp; He stated that they were concerned that agile development meant that they had to start at the beginning each time they started a new module.&nbsp; Fred provided clarification that they do not need to and that projects can easily proceed with agile development.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p><strong>Unified Communication</strong></p>\r\n<p>Provided Mohammad a presentation  regarding how to present it to upper management.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Compiled slides for WO 300\'s presentation on 1/4/11.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Prepared a status presentation to present to Ms.  Levine on 1/4/11.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Met with Mohammad on 1/4/11 to dicuss NISMS  and GPI scopes.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Mr. Samuels, Ms. Levine, Mr. Nedd, Beth, Dan and Tim S. on 1/5/11 regarding the Geospatial Publication Investment(GPI) and its scope.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Submitted email request to Mr.  Smauels on 1/3/11 in regards to the status of the New Media strategy.&nbsp;  He provided a verbal response that he had not submitted the newest  version to the teams.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on  1/4/11 to discuss GPI\'s status.&nbsp; We looked at strategy\'s to ensure that  we were pursuing the best approach since we inserted GPI into SLM after  the project had started.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p><strong>Unified Communication</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Mohammad to  discuss Unified Communication on 1/3/11.&nbsp; Forwarded him a presentation  regarding how to present it to upper management.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met  with Beth 1/4/11 regarding WO 300\'s presentation to Mike Nedd regarding  the status and the scope concerns.&nbsp; Compiled slides for their afternoon  presentation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Al\'Tariq, Mr. Lewis and myself met with Ms. Levine on 1/4/11 to discuss  GPI and AFMSS.&nbsp; Ms. Levine reviewed the information and informed us that  the ITIB would likely be postponed.&nbsp; She informed us that user groups  needed to be part of our effort and that a lead should be chosen outside  of WO300 and WO500.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Mohammad on 1/4/11 to dicuss NISMS  and GPI scopes.&nbsp; He was unsure of NISMS scope so we could not define  overlap.&nbsp; We disussed the need for a site where everyone could share  information about projects they are working on and the status.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with Mr. Samuels, Ms. Levine, Mr. Nedd, Beth, Dan and Tim S. on 1/5/11 regarding the Geospatial Publication Investment(GPI) and its scope.&nbsp; The GPI team proposed creating a Bureau wide effort instead of just a WO 300 effort.&nbsp; Ms. Levine and Mr. Need both agreed that it was a good goal.&nbsp; Ms. Levine reinforced that WO 300 needs to work with the other Directorates in order to gain buy in.&nbsp; Ms. Levine also stated that she wants an end user team established with a team lead.&nbsp; Beth agreed that this was a good idea and feasible.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Ms. Levine also announced that the ITIB will be postponed.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Other</strong></p>\r\n<p>Attended staff meeting on 1/4/11. Mr. Samuels emphasized the need to understand WO 500 goals and the roles that each of us play.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on  1/4/11 to discuss GPI\'s status.&nbsp; We looked at strategy\'s to ensure that  we were pursuing the best approach since we inserted GPI into SLM after  the project had started.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred to discuss NOC\'s  concerns on 1/6/11.&nbsp; He stated that they were concerned that agile  development meant that they had to start at the beginning each time they  started a new module.&nbsp; Fred provided clarification that they do not  need to and that projects can easily proceed with agile development.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>na</p>','<p>na</p>',2,4,'2012-01-06 18:38:49',NULL,'2012-01-13 18:01:10');
INSERT INTO `statusreport` (`id`,`employeeid`,`projectid`,`clientid`,`weekendingdate`,`activities`,`accomplishments`,`meetingsandpresentations`,`issues`,`itemsforcotr`,`status`,`createdby`,`datecreated`,`lastupdatedby`,`lastupdatedate`) VALUES 
 (13,6,1,1,'2012-01-06','<ul>\r\n<li>Assisted Naomi to prepare for a GeoComm project status brief with Ms. Levine.</li>\r\n<li>Made last changes to the draft SLM Acquisition Strategy template for now. &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Made last changes to the draft SLM Business Case template for now.</li>\r\n<li>Made last changes to the draft SLM Project Charter template for now.</li>\r\n<li>Had a few more discussions with Mr. Leonard Gore (from BLM GIS group) to discuss their current need for help in the area of GIS.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Had a WO-570 staff meeting</li>\r\n<li>Had a phone conference with the NOC</li>\r\n<li>Had a meeting status update from Mr. Samuels regarding a previous with GPI/GeoComm as their status in SLM</li>\r\n<li>Still worked on getting together some records management templates that we can add to the SLM repository. &nbsp;Currently we do not have any and have not found any to use. &nbsp;Will check with DOI to see if they have available template we can use.</li>\r\n<li>Made some changes to the SLM IM that Lauren gave back to me because the reviewer needed some clarity in one of the paragraphs. &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Reviewed the NOC SLM diagram that Gail sent me. &nbsp;Working on a list of question to send Gail regarding this diagram</li>\r\n<li>Review some GPI email (to get caught up with where they currently are)</li>\r\n<li>Reviewed &nbsp;one of BLM&rsquo;s Geo Spatial web portals that is currently under development.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Working on making the last changes to the SLM artifacts based on the changes I last made to the SLM technical handbook.</li>\r\n<li>Reviewed the roles and responsibilities for Walk the Walk Project Lead and Deputy Project Lead for out internal Support/Process Systems project.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12pt;\">Completed making changes to the draft SLM Acquisition Strategy template for now.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12pt;\">Completed making changes to the draft SLM Business Case template for now.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12pt;\">Completed making changes to the draft SLM Project Charter template for now.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12pt;\">Completed looking at the last two GeoComm documents for Naomi.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Had a phone conference with the NOC to discuss the latest version of the SLM technical manual 1-5-12. Had a phone conference with Gail, Dan and Preston (the other part of our SLM team) at the NOC to discuss and answer questions about their concerns with the latest version of the SLM.&nbsp; Gail and her team were under the impression that the SLM process did not support the Agile method of development.&nbsp; This was a big concern because of other constraints and restrictions they have to conform to.&nbsp; After providing clarity and examples of how the process was designed to use the NOC team was clear that the SLM does support Agile development.&nbsp; The meeting was very good and I will keep the NOC updated with where we are with getting the SLM process approved. &nbsp;The NOC and to have a face to face via VTC before the end of January 2012.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Met with Mr. Samuels to discuss the latest meeting with Ms. Levine regarding GPI/GeoComm 1-5-12. &nbsp;We discuss a variety of topics from SLM, current BLM systems/programs to BLM culture, and AFMSS.&nbsp; The main purpose of the discussion was to inform me that Ms. Levine want to represent the current status of GPI/GeoComm using the swirl diagrams that we used when we gave her the SLM presentation a few months ago.&nbsp; I&rsquo;ll have to get the status from Naomi and see how we can incorporate the GPI/GeoComm status information in that type of diagram.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Met with Mr. Leonard Gore and 2 others to discuss the use of GIS in their area 1-3-12. &nbsp;They discuss area that they need help in (using resources more effective)</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Met with Mr. Leonard Gore briefly to clarify our discussion the day before 1-5-12. They wanted to know they can better use existing resources (Enterprise GIS) and how BLM can better use its people and technology</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Had our WO-570 staff meeting 1-4-12.&nbsp; Gave a status/update of what we are currently working on.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: #fafafa; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">None at this time</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: #fafafa; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">None at this time</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',2,4,'2012-01-06 20:06:31',6,'2012-01-13 18:02:19'),
 (14,6,1,1,'2012-01-13','<ul>\r\n<li>Still worked on getting together some records management templates that we can add to the SLM repository. &nbsp;Currently we do not have any and have not found any to use. &nbsp;Will check with DOI to see if they have available template we can use.</li>\r\n<li>Working on a list of question to send Gail regarding this diagram</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Still working on making the last changes to some of the SLM artifacts based on the changes I last made to the SLM technical handbook.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Had discussion with Naomi and Mr. Lewis regarding the GeoComm project.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Working on making some suggestion for the GeoComm project.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Working on making a list of suggested next actions for the GeoComm project.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Checked on the status of the SLM IM. &nbsp;Currently there is no new updated status for the SLM IM.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Had discussion with Naomi as regards to the New Media Project.</li>\r\n<li>From and SLM perspective: Currently looking into (researching) what it will take to pull together a basic Enterprise Architecture (EA) program. EA is very critical and is a required component of the SLM process. Projects cannot successfully progress through the SLM process without involving the area of EA.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n<div></div>\r\n</p>','<ul>\r\n<li>Completed making a good number of changes to the SLM technical manual in an effort to finalize this draft version before it goes out to be reviewed.</li>\r\n<li>Completed doing some basic research on Enterprise Architecture programs. &nbsp;Will need to do some further investigations on this.</li>\r\n</ul>','<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Had several conversations/discussions with Naomi through the week regarding the current status of GeoComm. 1-9-2012 through 1-13-2012. &nbsp;Had several discussion and brainstorming session as to how to get the GeoComm group moving forward to they can make progress. We came up with several options that we need to discuss with Mr. Samuels before we make the recommendation to the GeoComm group. &nbsp;As soon as complete and outline our suggestions/recommendations we will be submitting them to Mr. Samuels for his review and feedback.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Had a discussion with Naomi and Mr. Lewis 1-10-2012. &nbsp;Discussed the best way to get everyone that is a support system to GeoComm onboard and apart of the process for building the new GeoComm system.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Had a discussion/meeting with Naomi on 1-11-2012 regarding the need for a strong Enterprise Architecture (EA) program in order to ensure projects efforts are not duplicated and also having the ability to take advantage (piggy back) of an existing system.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Had a meeting with Naomi regarding the New Media project 1-12-2012. Had a brainstorming session with Naomi as to making some recommendation/suggestions as how the New Media project should proceed. &nbsp;Discussed how they need to better define the communication problem they are looking to fix before getting too far down the process, discussed which groups of people are they trying to improve communications with. &nbsp; Discussed how they currently communicate with these groups and how do they envision to communicate with these groups in the future.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>','<p>None at this time.</p>','<p>None at this time.</p>',2,1,'2012-01-13 22:04:09',NULL,'2012-02-03 19:57:11'),
 (15,3,2,1,'2012-01-13','<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Began  updating the ITIB presentation on 1/9/12 to include updated scope and  ensure that it is worded broadly enough for executives per Ms. Levines  request during the WO 300 and WO 500 meeting.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth and the GPI team on 1/13/12 via conference call to discuss the overall status and the scope as agreed upon by WO 300 and WO 500.&nbsp;  The most immediate concern is for WO 300 to provide a clear scope.&nbsp; It  is best to consider modular development to meet business needs in a  logical manner.&nbsp; There is a concern about interim solutions.&nbsp; I spoke  with Al\'Tariq and we are going to review the IM preventing development  in other program areas at this point.</p>\r\n<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met with Michelle Thomas on 1/10/12 to dicuss the New Media Strategy. She stated that she believed that stakeholder engagement is very different from Public Affairs which is the same assessment Ronnie has made.&nbsp; Michelle believes that WO 600 does govern what is formally posted but other interactions fall within a gray area and the roles in that area should be shared by WO 500 &amp; WO 600 because Kaveh is using the &ldquo;BLM can&rsquo;t&rdquo; in areas where BLM may be allowed.&nbsp; (When sharing this information, she asked that we not state that &ldquo;Michelle said&rdquo; because she still works with Kaveh).</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>Researched internal New Media proof of concept and sent a proposal  via email to Al\'Tariq on 1/12/12.&nbsp; The research included meeting with  Fred on 1/12/12 to discuss available technologies.</p>\r\n<p>Al\'Tariq  provided a copy of WO 600\'s (Kaveh\'s) email regarding the New Media  Strategy on 1/12/12.&nbsp; The email stated that WO 600 would not support the  strategy as currently written. I provided email feedback to Al\'Tariq on  1/12/12 regarding points that were not necessarily accurate to the  strategy.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq on 1/13/12 to discuss the New Media  Strategy overall and how to work with WO 600 to gain support.&nbsp; We  discussed the overall pupose and possibly pursuing an internal proof of  concept only&nbsp; at this time and it may provide us a basis to provide a  stakeholder engagement proof of concept at a later date. We also  discussed what we could agree to in WO 600\'s email. I will provide  Al\'Tariq with some feedback on how to reword items.</p>\r\n<p>Worked with Kyla on 1/13/12 to revise the Strategy.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 1/11/12 to discuss  the need for a strong EA in order to ensure projects arent duplicated  and arent conflicting in general.</p>','<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Began  updating the ITIB presentation on 1/9/12 to include updated scope and  ensure that it is worded broadly enough for executives per Ms. Levines  request during the WO 300 and WO 500 meeting.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth and the GPI team on 1/13/12 via conference call to discuss the overall status and the scope as agreed upon by WO 300 and WO 500.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met with Michelle Thomas on 1/10/12 to dicuss the New Media Strategy. </span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>Researched internal New Media proof of concept and sent a proposal  via email to Al\'Tariq on 1/12/12.&nbsp; The research included meeting with  Fred on 1/12/12 to discuss available technologies.</p>\r\n<p>Provided email feedback to Al\'Tariq on  1/12/12 regarding points that were not necessarily accurate to the  strategy in regards to WO 600\'s email.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq on 1/13/12 to discuss the New Media  Strategy overall and how to work with WO 600 to gain support.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Worked with Kyla on 1/13/12 to revise the Strategy.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 1/11/12 to discuss  the need for a strong EA in order to ensure projects arent duplicated  and arent conflicting in general.</p>','<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth and the GPI team on 1/13/12 via conference call to discuss the overall status and the scope as agreed upon by WO 300 and WO 500.&nbsp;  The most immediate concern is for WO 300 to provide a clear scope.&nbsp; It  is best to consider modular development to meet business needs in a  logical manner.&nbsp; There is a concern about interim solutions.&nbsp; I spoke  with Al\'Tariq and we are going to review the IM preventing development  in other program areas at this point.</p>\r\n<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Met with Michelle Thomas on 1/10/12 to dicuss the New Media Strategy. She stated that she believed that stakeholder engagement is very different from Public Affairs which is the same assessment Ronnie has made.&nbsp; Michelle believes that WO 600 does govern what is formally posted but other interactions fall within a gray area and the roles in that area should be shared by WO 500 &amp; WO 600 because Kaveh is using the &ldquo;BLM can&rsquo;t&rdquo; in areas where BLM may be allowed.&nbsp; (When sharing this information, she asked that we not state that &ldquo;Michelle said&rdquo; because she still works with Kaveh).</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq on 1/13/12 to discuss the New Media  Strategy overall and how to work with WO 600 to gain support.&nbsp; We  discussed the overall pupose and possibly pursuing an internal proof of  concept only&nbsp; at this time and it may provide us a basis to provide a  stakeholder engagement proof of concept at a later date. We also  discussed what we could agree to in WO 600\'s email. I will provide  Al\'Tariq with some feedback on how to reword items.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 1/11/12 to discuss  the need for a strong EA in order to ensure projects arent duplicated  and arent conflicting in general.</p>','<p>na</p>','<p>na</p>',2,4,'2012-01-13 22:38:07',3,'2012-01-20 00:23:26'),
